getFieldsString

public java.lang.String getFieldsString()
Get this interpretation's data as a pipe-delimited string of fields specific to the type and implementation.

This implementation gives integer values for: year|month|day|hour|minute|second|ampm|timezone

  • "-1" identifies "empty" values.
  • year is the year (i.e. 2007)
  • month ranges from 0=January to 11=December
  • day ranges from 1 to N
  • hour ranges from 0 to 11
  • ampm: 1=AM; 2=PM
  • timezone is the millis offset from GMT (i.e. 28800000 for MDT)

Specified by:
getFieldsString in interface Interpretation

hasValidParse

public boolean hasValidParse()
Determine whether this interpretation's parse is valid.

Currently, this checks for the condition of parsing only two from month, day, year when there appears to be three constituents.

getScore

public double getScore()
This returns a weighted score for the completeness of the interpretation. Each date and time part carries the following weights: year 25 month 20 day 15 hour 20 minute 10 second 5 millis 5

collidesWith

public boolean collidesWith(Interpretation other)
Determine whether this interpretation collides with another.

If two interpretations do not collide then they can simultaneously co-exist and cooperatively define an entity. For example a date and a time would not collide but a date and a date would.
